National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan spoke with Ibrahim Kalin, Spokesperson and Chief Advisor to the President of Turkey. Sullivan expressed the Biden Administration's desire to improve U.S.-Turkey relations and work together on common goals. He emphasized the importance of strengthening transatlantic security through NATO and voiced concerns about Turkey's acquisition of the Russian S-400 missile system. Sullivan also welcomed the resumption of talks between Turkey and Greece and expressed support for the United Nations Secretary General's plans to resume talks on Cyprus. Additionally, he reiterated the Biden administration's commitment to supporting democratic institutions and the rule of law. Both parties agreed to collaborate on global challenges such as the COVID-19 pandemic and climate change, as well as consult on regional issues of mutual concern.